{
  "id": "019d286a-f2d7-7750-81b8-3320287dd9de",
  "content": "## Augmenter Implementation\n\n### StructuredAugmenter\n\nFormats sources into a structured prompt with metadata and citation markers.\n\nOutput format:\n```\n[System prompt — configurable, has built-in default]\n\nContext from organizational knowledge:\n\n[1] (score: 0.94, source: src/auth.rs:45-80, type: function)\nThe authenticate() function validates JWT tokens...\n\n[2] (score: 0.91, source: docs/auth-design.md, type: markdown)\nAuthentication uses RS256 signing...\n\n[3] (score: 0.87, via: depends_on auth.rs, type: function)\nThe middleware chain calls authenticate() before...\n\nAnswer the following question using ONLY the context above.\nCite sources using [N] notation.\nQuestion: {query}\n```\n\nSources marked `via:` indicate graph-expanded entries (not direct vector matches).\n\n\n### Token budget (D64)\n\nModel-aware auto-sizing by default:\n```\navailable = generator.context_window() * (1.0 - reserve_for_answer)\n```\n\nManual override: set `max_context_tokens > 0` in config. Token estimation: chars / 4 heuristic (swappable via Augmenter trait).\n\nSources are packed by score until budget is exhausted. Truncated sources are counted in metrics.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-02-m3.2-rag-pipeline-design.md",
